---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Operating System Architecture — Wychwood Partners"
  description="Design and install a capital-disciplined operating system for growth-stage and private equity-backed businesses."
>
  <main class="shell py-14">
    <a
      href="/services/"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))] hover:text-[rgb(var(--text))] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[rgba(var(--brand-accent),0.55)] focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-[rgb(var(--surface))]"
    >
      ← Back to services
    </a>
    <h1>Operating System Architecture</h1>

    <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
      An operating system that makes execution predictable: clear ownership, decision rights, unit economics, and a weekly rhythm that holds.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
      It connects strategy to day-to-day control — without adding bureaucracy. If nobody owns the number, it is just reporting.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="card p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold">What it includes</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>• A metrics hierarchy that ladders from team to exec to board.</li>
          <li>• Unit economics governance with clear variance thresholds.</li>
          <li>• Decision rights, escalation paths, and meeting outputs.</li>
          <li>• A weekly execution cadence tied to priorities and capital allocation.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold">When it’s needed</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>• Growth is outrunning founder-led execution.</li>
          <li>• Performance is volatile: margin drifts, targets slip, and surprises keep landing late.</li>
          <li>• The board can’t see what’s really happening (or why).</li>
          <li>• Expansion is adding sites, markets, products, or teams.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Outcomes</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>• Board-ready performance visibility.</li>
          <li>• Faster decisions — and fewer decisions reopened the following week.</li>
          <li>• Clear ownership and accountability that sticks.</li>
          <li>• Predictable execution across teams and sites.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 card p-8">
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold">Assess your operating system</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
        In 30 minutes we’ll pinpoint where ownership, metrics, and cadence are breaking down — and define the fixes required. The aim is simple: fewer surprises, tighter follow-through.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] bg-[rgb(var(--brand-anchor))] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white transition hover:opacity-95"
          >Book a call</a
        >
        <a
          href="/case-studies"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] border border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface-elevated))] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] transition hover:bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))]"
          >View case studies</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-16 border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))] pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Related frameworks & case studies</h2>

      <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <a
          href="/frameworks/operating-system/"
          class="group card cursor-pointer p-6 transition hover:shadow-md hover:bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[rgba(var(--brand-accent),0.55)] focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-[rgb(var(--surface))]"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Operating System Framework</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            How decision rights, unit economics, and execution rhythm fit together in practice.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">
            View framework <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </p>
        </a>

        <a
          href="/case-studies/multi-acquisition-integration/"
          class="group card cursor-pointer p-6 transition hover:shadow-md hover:bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[rgba(var(--brand-accent),0.55)] focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-[rgb(var(--surface))]"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">M&A Integration Case Study</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            Buy-side integration across three acquisitions, including decisive leadership changes.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">
            Read case study <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </p>
        </a>

        <a
          href="/case-studies/scaling-multi-state-auto-platform/"
          class="group card cursor-pointer p-6 transition hover:shadow-md hover:bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[rgba(var(--brand-accent),0.55)] focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-[rgb(var(--surface))]"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Multi-State Platform Scaling</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            Building operational consistency across regulated, asset-heavy multi-site operations.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">
            Read case study <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
